definition: to pile up/to put layer upon layer/(Tw) (computing) stack
to pile up/to heap up/a mass/pile/heap/stack/large amount
to fold/to fold over in layers/to furl/to layer/to pile up/to repeat/to duplicate

sentences.english: Some enclosures are stackable or can be placed on casters.
sentences.chinese: 有些外壳可以堆叠，也可以放在脚轮上。

sentences.english: This is a standard stackable letter tray.
sentences.chinese: 这是一个标准的堆叠信件托盘。

sentences.english: Owners should ensure the mat is “never stacked, ” the agency said.
sentences.chinese: 车主应保证自选脚垫没有堆叠。

sentences.english: Rather, the years pile on like blankets, existing all at once.
sentences.chinese: 这么说吧，年份像毯子一样堆叠，相互并列同时存在。

sentences.english: With time elapsing, the flaps collapse up on his clapper' s lap.
sentences.chinese: 随着时光流逝，袋盖在拍手者的膝上堆叠起来。

sentences.english: The parcels were therefore taken out, stacked and covered with tarpaulins.
sentences.chinese: 包裹，因此取出，堆叠，且覆盖了一层防水布。

sentences.english: Valve overlap is held to a minimum on turbo-charged engines.
sentences.chinese: 在涡轮增压发起机上气门堆叠角被连结在一个最小值。

sentences.english: Behind them black clouds piled one atop another against a blood-red sky.
sentences.chinese: 在他们身后是血红天空上的一团相互堆叠着的黑云。

sentences.english: The little girl piled one paper box  on top of the other.
sentences.chinese: 小女孩把一个纸箱子堆叠在另一个之上。

sentences.english: When we used the building block metaphor earlier, we mentioned snapping or stacking blocks together.
sentences.chinese: 在前面使用构造块比喻时，我们提到要堆叠构造块。

sentences.english: Arrows and bullets no longer stack, but are not consumed.
sentences.chinese: 箭矢和子弹将不再堆叠，并且不能被买卖。

sentences.english: Does the traveller clearly define all the drilling parameters including stack height?
sentences.chinese: 钻孔机是否能够清楚地定义钻孔参数，包括堆叠厚度？

sentences.english: The set of stator laminations is arranged into a stack.
sentences.chinese: 该组定子叠片被布置成层叠或堆叠。

sentences.english: Stackable washers provide a great solution for laundry areas in tight quarters.
sentences.chinese: 可堆叠的垫圈狭小提供洗衣领域的最佳解决方案。

sentences.english: The elements of the control-flow stack are system-compilation data types.
sentences.chinese: 在流程控制堆叠上的元素是系统编译型别。

sentences.english: Never stack multiple rows of tabs to control a single piece of content.
sentences.chinese: 从来没有堆叠多个列的标签来控制一块的内容。

definition: lit. to pile up (bricks)/to pack/fig. to pad out (writing with fancy phrases)/ornate rhetoric
to fold/to fold over in layers/to furl/to layer/to pile up/to repeat/to duplicate
to pile up layer upon layer
variant of 重疊|重叠[chong2 die2]
to overlap/to superimpose/to telescope/to run together/to duplicate/one over another/superposition/an overlap/redundancy/reduplication (in Chinese grammar, e.g. 散散步[san4 san4 bu4] to have a stroll)
